1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Ever wonder why we resist change, even when it’s better?

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,600
This is status quo bias, a tendency to favor the familiar over the unknown.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:14,000
Studies show it’s not just laziness; it’s wired in our brains.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,200
We feel safer sticking with what we know.

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:21,600
People often pay more for old habits than exploring new options.

6
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:24,800
We fear loss more than we crave gain.

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:29,600
Recognizing this bias empowers us to make better choices and embrace change.

8
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,000
Ready to challenge your status quo?

9
